<item>
            <title>[LU-17850] use LINUXRELEASE instead of &quot;uname -r&quot; in lustre.spec.in</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17850</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In a container or chroot environment, &quot;uname -r&quot; reports the host instead of the target kernel version. We should use the LINUXRELEASE variable which is configured in config/lustre-build-linux.m4 with the value from UTS_RELEASE.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
